fields.bio:
I'm Mahammed Touray, a full-stack developer with three years of experience in Python and Node.js. Currently at InSIST Global, I excel in creating robust, scalable applications.

- Front-End: HTML, CSS, JavaScript

I'm passionate about learning and ready to tackle new challenges. Let's turn your ideas into reality with high-quality code and efficient solutions.

What I Look For:

Reliability: Consistent and timely completion of tasks.
Attention to Detail: High-quality and error-free work.
Problem-Solving Skills: Ability to tackle challenges and find effective solutions.

If you're a dedicated freelancer ready to take on small but impactful tasks, let's connect and collaborate!

fields.title: Cloud Business Website Development
fields.description:
I need a proficient website developer who can create a comprehensive website for my cloud business. This website will be aimed at small business owners and will need to be professional, easy to navigate, and comprehensive.

Key features to include:

- An 'About Us' section
- Detailed 'Services Offered' section
- Clearly outlined 'Pricing and Plans'
- A 'booking demos' feature
- A login database for visitors
- An integration with our existing portal

Ideal candidates should submit their past work, preferably with similar business-targeted websites. Experience in integrating login databases and booking features will be highly valued.

There is a website called Vultr... want something close to that.
fields.required_skills: PHP, Website Design, Graphic Design, MySQL HTML

fields.title: ConvertKit API Integration for Email Pre-Population
fields.description:
I'm looking for a developer proficient in ConvertKit API to help with integrating it with my website. Specifically, I need assistance with pre-populating email addresses in the subscriber form using a URL parameter. This job involves:

- Setting up ConvertKit API integration with my website
- Implementing the required pre-population mechanism using a URL parameter

The error I get it:

populate-email.js:23 Error parsing JSON:
SyntaxError: Unexpected token '<', "
<!DOCTYPE "... is not valid JSON
at JSON.parse (<anonymous>)
at populate-email.js:15:24
(anonymous) @ populate-email.js:23

Ideal candidates for this project should have:
- Proficiency with ConvertKit API and prior experience in integrating it with websites
- A strong understanding of implementing URL parameters for pre-populating form fields
- The ability to troubleshoot and identify any issues that may arise during the integration process

Please note: I am only looking for assistance with the technical aspects of integrating
fields.required_skills: PHP, Java, JavaScript, Google App Engine, JSON

fields.title: UI/UX Designer Needed to Create Concept in Figma
fields.description:
I am looking for a talented UI/UX designer to help me design a concept in Figma.
The project involves creating wireframes, prototypes, and final UI designs based on my initial
ideas and requirements.

Responsibilities

- Develop wireframes and prototypes
- Design a user-friendly and visually appealing UI
- Collaborate with me to iterate on designs based on feedback
- Deliver polished and high-quality final designs in Figma

Requirements
- Proven experience in UI/UX design
- Proficiency in Figma
- Strong portfolio showcasing relevant work
- Excellent communication skills
- Attention to detail and creativity

If you are passionate about designing exceptional user interfaces and have the skills to bring 
concepts to life in Figma, please apply with your portfolio and relevant experience.

Looking forward to working with you!
